com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel.groovy.api

Interface IBswmdModelDefRefsApi


  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public interface IBswmdModelDefRefsApi
    TIBswmdModelDefRefsApi provides methods to retrieve generated DefRef instances from the SIP without knowing the correct java/groovy imports.
    The sipDefRef API provides access to retrieve generated DefRef instances from the SIP without knowing the correct Java/Groovy imports. This is mainly useful in script files, where no IDE helps with the imports.

    If you are using an Automation Script Project you can ignore this API and use the DefRefs provided by the generated classes, which is superior to this API, because they are typesafe and compile time checked.

    • Method Detail

      • getAt

        @PublishedMethod
DefRef getAt(java.lang.String defRefString)
        Returns the DefRef by the passed defRefString.

        If the defRefString contains a '/' the method tries to retrieve the DefRef by the full AUTOSAR definition path.

        If the shortName does not contain any '/' the method tries to find the definition with the passed short name. The name must be unique in the whole SIP.

        Parameters:
        defRefString - the definition string or the short name of the definition
        Returns:
        the DefRef
        Throws:
        groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException -
        • If the shortName is not unique in the SIP. Then please try to specify the full definition path.
        • If the shortName was not found in the SIP.
